<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/269</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Page</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>481. Detention of Enrico Ajello. Present case again to Italian
                            Government, calling particular attention to fact Ajello born New York
                            City March 15, 1882. Ajello resided this country continuously since
                            birth, with exception short business trip Italy 1906. Refer Ghiloni
                            case. Ask release. Report fully.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>